body:
# Slack Messages

Send, update, delete, and schedule messages in Slack channels and DMs using the Web API. All message operations require a bot token (`xoxb-`) with the `chat:write` scope. See [[slack]] for authentication setup.

## Send a Message

```javascript
import { WebClient } from "@slack/web-api";

const slack = new WebClient(process.env.SLACK_BOT_TOKEN);

const result = await slack.chat.postMessage({
  channel: "C0123456789",
  text: "Hello from the agent!",
  blocks: [
    {
      type: "section",
      text: {
        type: "mrkdwn",
        text: "*Hello from the agent!*\nThis message uses Block Kit."
      }
    }
  ]
});

console.log(result.ts); // Message timestamp (unique ID)
```

The `text` field is the fallback for notifications and accessibility. Always include it even when using `blocks`. See [[slack/block-kit]] for building rich layouts.

## Update a Message

```javascript
await slack.chat.update({
  channel: "C0123456789",
  ts: "1234567890.123456",  // Original message timestamp
  text: "Updated message text",
  blocks: [
    {
      type: "section",
      text: { type: "mrkdwn", text: "*Updated content*" }
    }
  ]
});
```

Use the `ts` (timestamp) returned from `chat.postMessage` to identify the message to update.

## Delete a Message

```javascript
await slack.chat.delete({
  channel: "C0123456789",
  ts: "1234567890.123456"
});
```

Bots can only delete messages they posted. Users can delete their own messages with a user token.

## Threads

Reply in a thread by setting `thread_ts` to the parent message timestamp:

```javascript
await slack.chat.postMessage({
  channel: "C0123456789",
  thread_ts: "1234567890.123456",  // Parent message ts
  text: "This is a threaded reply"
});
```

Set `reply_broadcast: true` to also post the reply to the channel ("Also send to channel" checkbox).

## Formatting

Slack uses `mrkdwn` (not standard Markdown) for text formatting:

| Syntax | Result |
|--------|--------|
| `*bold*` | **bold** |
| `_italic_` | _italic_ |
| `~strike~` | ~~strike~~ |
| `` `code` `` | `code` |
| ` ```code block``` ` | code block |
| `<@U0123456>` | @mention user |
| `<#C0123456>` | #mention channel |
| `<!here>` | @here |
| `<!channel>` | @channel |

## Scheduling

```javascript
await slack.chat.scheduleMessage({
  channel: "C0123456789",
  text: "This message will arrive in the future",
  post_at: Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000) + 3600  // Unix timestamp, 1 hour from now
});
```

Scheduled messages can be listed with `chat.scheduledMessages.list` and cancelled before delivery.
